data.chText: 在…底下；隐藏（或掩盖）在下面
data.enText: under or below sth else, especially when it is hidden or covered by the thing on top
The coin rolled underneath the piano.

data.chText: 即使里面穿一件毛衣，这件外套也太大了。
data.enText: This jacket's too big, even with a sweater underneath.

data.chText: （指真实的感情或性格）在…表象之下
data.enText: used to talk about sb's real feelings or character, as opposed to the way they seem to be

data.chText: 她外表冷静，其实内心十分害怕。
data.enText: Underneath her cool exterior she was really very frightened.

data.chText: 他表面脾气暴躁，实则菩萨心肠。
data.enText: He seems bad-tempered, but he's very soft-hearted underneath.

data.chText: （物体的）下表面，底面，底部，下部
data.enText: the lower surface or part of sth

data.chText: 她拉开抽屉仔细查看底部。
data.enText: She pulled the drawer out and examined the underneath carefully.

means: (指真实的感情或性格)在…表象之下

ex.chText: 两个老人正在树下下棋。
ex.enText: Two old men are playing chess under the tree.
Your bag is under the bed.
You'd better lie under a blanket.

synonyms.bx: 指某物在另一物的下面或底下，两者之间有无一定距离均可。

ex.chText: 有些城市位于海平面以下。
ex.enText: Some cities are below sea level.

ex.chText: 你听到窗户下面的院子里有人在说话吗？
ex.enText: Have you heard voices in the courtyard below your window?

synonyms.bx: 指某物所处的位置低于另一物。

ex.chText: 很多游客喜欢脚下踩着温暖沙子的感觉。
ex.enText: Many tourists enjoy feeling the warm sand beneath their feet.

ex.chText: 在银色的月光下，大海更加吸引人。
ex.enText: Beneath the silvery moon, the sea is more attractive.
They slept outside beneath the stars.

synonyms.bx: 指所处位置时，与 under, below 基本同义，但有时强调在某物的正下方，而且较富有文学性。

ex.chText: 我会把钥匙放在垫子下面。
ex.enText: I'll leave the key underneath the mat.

ex.chText: 他以前常用一顶棒球帽裹住满头金发。
ex.enText: He used to hide his blonde hair underneath a baseball cap.

ex.chText: 甚至她自己也忘了藏在地板下面的盒子。
ex.enText: Even she herself has forgotten about the box underneath the floorboards.

synonyms.bx: 与 under 的意思相近，但含有将某物隐藏或遮盖起来之意。

tr: under or below an object or a surface
at a lower place or level
example: we could see the original painting underneath
a house with a good foundation underneath

tr: on the lower or downward side
example: a chest of drawers all scratched underneath

value.def: If one thing is underneath another, it is directly under it, and may be covered or hidden by it.

example.ex: The device exploded underneath a van.
example.tran: 该装置在一辆货车底下发生了爆炸。

example.ex: ...using dogs to locate people trapped underneath collapsed buildings.
example.tran: 利用狗来寻找被困在倒塌的楼房下面的人

example.ex: ...a table for two underneath the olive trees...
example.tran: 橄榄树下的一张两人桌

example.ex: Her apartment was underneath a bar, called 'The Lift'.
example.tran: 她的公寓在一个叫“醒神”的酒吧下面。

example.ex: He has on a denim shirt with a T-shirt underneath.
example.tran: 他穿了一件牛仔衬衫，里面套了件T恤。

example.ex: ...if we could maybe pull back a bit of this carpet to see what's underneath...
example.tran: 我们能否把这块地毯往后拉一拉，看底下是什么东西

example.ex: The shooting-range is lit from underneath by rows of ruby-red light fittings.
example.tran: 射击场被一排排深红色的灯光设备从下面照亮了。

gramarinfo.label: n ADV, ADV after v, <l>be</l> ADV, <l>from</l> ADV

value.def: The part of something which is underneath is the part which normally touches the ground or faces towards the ground.

example.ex: Check the actual construction of the chair by looking underneath...
example.tran: 看看椅子的下面，检查一下它的实际构造。

example.ex: The sand martin is a brown bird with white underneath...
example.tran: 崖沙燕是一种褐羽白腹的鸟。

example.ex: His bare feet were smooth on top and rough-skinned underneath.
example.tran: 他赤裸的双脚脚面很光滑，脚底却很粗糙。

example.ex: Some objects had got entangled with the underneath mechanism of the engine.
example.tran: 一些东西缠在了发动机下面的机件上。

example.ex: Now I know what the underneath of a car looks like.
example.tran: 现在我知道汽车的底部是什么样子了。

value.def: You use underneath when talking about feelings and emotions that people do not show in their behaviour.

example.ex: He was as violent as Nick underneath...
example.tran: 在内心深处，他和尼克一样暴躁不安。

example.ex: Underneath, Sofia was deeply committed to her husband.
example.tran: 索菲娅从内心里对丈夫忠贞不贰。

example.ex: Underneath his outgoing behaviour Luke was shy.
example.tran: 在外向活泼的外表下，卢克其实很害羞。
